      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "**Frontend RUM (Real User Monitoring) for the Angular SPA via Grafana Faro.** The `faro` receiver + traces/logs pipeline are **live** in the otel-collector (browser \u2192 collector \u2192 Grafana Cloud). Panels populate **once the Angular app is instrumented with the Faro Web SDK**. Data model: Faro beacon \u2192 OTLP \u2192 Loki (labels `service_name`=Faro app, `deployment_environment`, `kind`\u2208{log,measurement,exception,event}) + Tempo (browser spans). Web-Vitals thresholds follow Google\u2019s good/needs-improvement/poor bands.\n\n| Section | What it answers |\n|---|---|\n| **Overview** | Session count, exception count, Web-Vitals KPIs (LCP / INP / CLS / FCP / TTFB) and browser diversity |\n| **Core Web Vitals (p75)** | p75 stat cards + trend lines for all five Web-Vitals metrics |\n| **Errors & exceptions** | Exception rate over time, top browsers by exceptions, raw exception log stream |\n| **Sessions & audience** | Session trend, browser + OS/mobile breakdown |\n| **Live RUM logs & browser traces** | Full Faro event stream and Tempo browser trace list |",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "About this dashboard",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
